A woman died and three other people were injured when a truck and a car collided on the N2 northbound just after the M7 interchange in Durban, paramedics said on Sunday. Rescue Care paramedics arrived on the scene to find carnage , Rescue Care spokesperson Ceron Lennox said. A truck had collided with a car in the fast lane of the busy highway. It was alleged that the car had broken down, but this would be investigated by police. Paramedics found that one of the car passengers had sustained multiple injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for her. She was declared dead on the scene. A passenger from the car and two passengers from the truck sustained moderate injuries and were stabilised on the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for the further care they required, Lennox said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.